author: Jenny Hsu
title: Oil Prices Rise; Gains Likely Capped Due to Oversupply
text: 0201 GMT [Dow Jones] Crude oil prices pare earlier losses mainly due to bargain-hunting after prices dropped around 2% overnight on oversupply concerns, says a Singapore-based trader. The U.S. energy department said domestic crude-oil inventories increased by 8 million barrels in the week ended Oct. 16, far exceeding market expectations of an 3.5-million barrel increase. “As China’s demand cools down, we will see more pressure on prices,” he says, but notes the weaker dollar is giving oil prices some support.
